<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[227,348,1154,1180]" box="[227,348,1154,1180]" pageId="30" pageNumber="97">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,1154,1180]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="97" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,1154,1180]" pageId="30" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[226,1436,1201,1300]" pageId="30" pageNumber="97">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1884" box="[352,512,1201,1227]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Aphelaeceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="30" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[352,512,1201,1227]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="97">Aphelaeceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reaching about 
<quantity box="[698,794,1202,1228]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="30" pageNumber="97" unit="mm" value="130.0">130 mm</quantity>
conch diameter. Conch with weakly compressed whorl profile (ww/wh ~ 0.65); venter double-keeled with narrow longitudinal groove; flanks convergent, umbilical margin subangular, umbilical wall oblique, weakly concave. Shell surface nearly smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
